Question 6 : Symmetric Tree (Not very Clear...See Again)

Leetcode : 101

Mirror means: (Draw tree for better visualisation)
    - Left child of left subtree == Right child of right subtree
    - Right child of left subtree == Left child of right subtree

'isMirror' Method : Base Cases (Stopping Conditions) :
- If both nodes are null, we've reached the end of both branches simultaneously. This is symmetric. Return true.
- One is null, one isn't: If one side has a node but the other doesn't, the tree is lopsided. Return false.

If both nodes exist, three things must be true for them to be mirrors:
- Values match: left.val == right.val.
- Outer branches match: The far-left of the left subtree must match the far-right of the right subtree :
  (isMirror(left.left, right.right)).
- Inner branches match: The inner-right of the left subtree must match the inner-left of the right subtree :
  (isMirror(left.right, right.left)).

