Question 8 : Depth First Search

Leetcode : 543

The diameter is the longest path between any two nodes in the tree.
Important: the path may or may not pass through the root.

💡 Key Idea
At every node, think about two things:
- Height of the left subtree
- Height of the right subtree
If a path goes through this node, its length is: (left height) + (right height)
So: While computing height, we also update the maximum diameter seen so far.

