Question 13 : Validate Binary Search Tree (Not Clear...must see)
draw and try to visualise...

Leetcode : 98

A tree is a valid BST if:
- everything in the left subtree is < node.val
- everything in the right subtree is > node.val
- this must hold for the whole subtree, not only direct children

💡 Big idea behind the solution :
We give every node a range of allowed values : (min , max)
At every step we ask:
“Is this node’s value inside its allowed range?”
Then we pass updated ranges to its children.

We check min != null / max != null because:
- null means “there is no boundary yet.”
- And if we don’t check, Java would try to compare against null and crash with a NullPointerException.

